<subSubSection id="29897D4E3E8E599E4D61CC01DF02C298" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="common names">
<paragraph id="609BA374BD82BBDAB005FB14CCF5A12E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Common names.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F6414D46A6C1468FADCE090A66018A76" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Van 
<normalizedToken id="FE024B90AB3292079E0E8EDAE7427AB5" originalValue="Rooyenâ€™s">Rooyen's</normalizedToken>
aloe (English); vanrooyense-aalwyn (Afrikaans).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B105269258D0C75409ACE13511326CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="A71373121CCD9FB6D3C76BD69007635E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB8297742CC5E4359D0F398DB6AFDDBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Acaulescent plants; rosettes solitary, very rarely suckering to form small groups; with persistent dried leaves. 
<emphasis id="45DB6CF94570368485F85F3246C4AB2C" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leaves</emphasis>
densely rosulate, distinctly spreading, reflexed, upper surface shiny pale green, with pale milky green to whitish, variously shaped spots, often more or less confluent in transverse bands, lower surface uniformly milky green, rarely with longitudinal darker greenish striations, deltoid-lanceolate, attenuate, 12-15 cm long, 6-8 cm wide, apex dry, sometimes with small teeth at keel near apex; margins whitish, near-translucent, with very pungent, brownish-orange, recurved teeth, 3-4 mm long, 3-4 mm apart; exudate clear, drying purplish. 
<emphasis id="D1FA2B18FC10637F87D4F364EE214BB1" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Inflorescence</emphasis>
0.5-0.8 m high, erect, 1- or 2-branched below middle. 
<emphasis id="BF152263E4F0D9C2C8712E65D7760E32" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Racemes</emphasis>
cylindrical to slightly conical, 25-47 cm long, 7-9 cm wide, lax. 
<emphasis id="E880617A3EB1825D2C38273B243D020F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Floral bracts</emphasis>
8-10 mm long. 
<emphasis id="6A45C4524C0B44B67283D957014D2BAD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pedicels</emphasis>
8-10 mm long. 
<emphasis id="10D2A3B0EEDAE0DCF81EDD136397F086" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowers</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="504B9D7D4D6040C957A4723EAF67F578" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">perianth</emphasis>
orange or red, 33-38 mm long, 8-10 mm across ovary, abruptly constricted above ovary to form globose basal swelling, widening towards wide open mouth, cylindrical-trigonous; outer segments free for 8-15 mm; 
<emphasis id="A650F4FDB136863151A296C95AC43A01" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">stamens</emphasis>
exserted up to 3 mm; 
<emphasis id="F48352E89AD7E59E28CD89BEF32A6440" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">style</emphasis>
slightly exserted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A9E9C303D965B827A72F4F9A51BC334" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="flowering time">
<paragraph id="FA9139615C3B55CF5F94BB489EB6CD2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flowering time.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="30ECF585C7E05C23BF9D25731CC96024" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">October-November.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4513DB63C267B1430C495426E01D1A09" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="62AA616F56DE66FD1E6FB2BCB078A68C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C0D2618F265D06D7D83EC190EF84730" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thornveld savannah.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBCC57388860DA3AF5FC1018FDC4E9AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="A970A0CC5510935204F72D46CF3FD7DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C07284AE1DF1C2649C49FDD43336C07" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="062750BEC5DE638740C6486DFF36D3F6" authorityName="Gideon F. Sm. &amp; N. R. Crouch" authorityYear="2006" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe vanrooyenii" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vanrooyenii">
<emphasis id="E344AB3546F44586E032BC40D4A33AB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe vanrooyenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other maculate aloes in KwaZulu-Natal (
<taxonomicName id="99EB56535243C6644EE71D3511345698" authorityName="Reynolds" authorityYear="1937" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe dewetii" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewetii">
<emphasis id="754BF5A0D62112A2DB1332B74BDE9EDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe dewetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="11CA386A3A195B5C086EBA57AC6CB49D" authority="subsp. maculata" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe maculata subsp. maculata" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maculata" subSpecies="maculata">Aloe maculata subsp. maculata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="01D2CC920325330BB3E87B78E19BB317" authorityName="Reynolds" authorityYear="1937" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe mudenensis" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mudenensis">
<emphasis id="C1966C05D0800B9A529487D4922D5A93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe mudenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BE972407E6A195B62FC56181C1F0D628" authorityName="Schoenland" authorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe parvibracteata" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvibracteata">
<emphasis id="004B3457FE7CBA0EF8D9BD0230E9BA6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe parvibracteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3D2223F4FD865E2514724431007A623C" authorityName="I. Verd. &amp; D. S. Hardy" authorityYear="1965" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe prinslooi" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prinslooi">
<emphasis id="3F8926556ACCEC9B09A899C9851DD32A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe prinslooi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="489631D0AABDF1CB6CA9DE5123EC6CB4" authorityName="Reynolds" authorityYear="1936" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe pruinosa" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis id="A4B98D96E519D7FE5819D41A9EA4767B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D193814A17842057789428887A2FB469" authorityName="Reynolds" authorityYear="1937" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe suffulta" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffulta">
<emphasis id="D48CFADCA1365339EB76E4504C15DAF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe suffulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0CB9DDA8CAC13D95F26C1E5D92CB3043" authorityName="Gideon F. Sm. &amp; N. R. Crouch" authorityYear="2006" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe vanrooyenii" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vanrooyenii">
<emphasis id="0B36E433BE32863E19974CEBC0FB4B4D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe vanrooyenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FA2A2820515378604C218826DA61AABA" authorityName="Gideon F. Sm. &amp; Figueiredo" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aloe viridiana" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridiana">
<emphasis id="7DB65A04BE6835987A49474A3CFE42C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aloe viridiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the 1- or 2-branched inflorescence with lax, cylindrical to slightly conical racemes (25-47 
<normalizedToken id="3218AC5B8A6DA5955588ED491954886B" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
7-9 cm) with pedicels 8-10 mm long. It is further characterised by the very large, erect fruit (25-28 
<normalizedToken id="8CCC20F38AEF353E1FD4B1449AC42E75" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
14-18 mm in fresh state), which cause the peduncle to bend towards the ground as it cannot support the weight of the large mature capsules. Flowers are orange or red, 33-38 mm long and with a globose basal swelling (8-10 mm diameter). Leaves are distinctly spreading and reflexed, 12-15 
<normalizedToken id="B10D5E6ECF39CBE936312846748360F1" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 cm and spotted on the upper surface, while the lower surface is rarely lineate. Marginal teeth are 3-4 mm long. This is the only early summer-flowering maculate aloe in KwaZulu-Natal (
<bibRefCitation id="8416513870932B1633AB5562341E765A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4102/abc.v36i1.342" author="Smith, GF" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="73 - 75" refId="B41" refString="Smith, GF, Crouch, NR, 2006. Aloe vanrooyenii: A distinctive new maculate aloe from KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. Bothalia 36: 73 - 75, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4102/abc.v36i1.342" title="Aloe vanrooyenii: A distinctive new maculate aloe from KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa." url="https://doi.org/10.4102/abc.v36i1.342" volume="36" year="2006">Smith and Crouch 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
